modules.description: This module offers set operations such as adding, removing, and combining elements of type `tydef`, along with querying and membership checks, while supporting ordered traversal and transformation via filtering, mapping, and folding. It works with structured sets `t` and sequence-based manipulations, enabling efficient data processing and ordered element management. Specific use cases include dynamic data aggregation, ordered data analysis, and seamless integration of set operations with sequence transformations.

provides set-based operations for managing structured elements, including addition, removal, combination, and traversal, with support for filtering, mapping, and folding. It handles ordered sequences and structured types, enabling dynamic data aggregation and transformation. Users can perform membership checks, element manipulation, and sequence-based processing. Examples include building ordered tag collections, merging log metadata, and analyzing structured data streams.

Processes and parses messages formatted according to RFC 5424, extracting structured data such as priority, timestamp, hostname, and message content. Implements functions to validate message syntax and extract components like facility, severity, and appname. Used to parse system logs from Unix-based systems and forward them to centralized logging services.

manages structured elements through set-based operations, supporting addition, removal, combination, and traversal with filtering, mapping, and folding. It works with ordered sequences and structured types, enabling dynamic data aggregation and transformation. Users can build ordered tag collections, merge log metadata, and analyze structured data streams. Key data types include sets and sequences, with operations for membership checks, element manipulation, and sequence processing.
